# LunCo headless server configuration — read by lunco-server.service.
# Copy to /opt/lunco/lunco-server.env and edit. Keep it root:lunco 0640.

# --- TLS (CA cert for sandbox.lunco.space) -----------------------------------
# These point at the SERVICE-LOCAL copy that the certbot deploy hook writes
# (NOT directly at /etc/letsencrypt — privkey there is root:root 0600 and the
# unprivileged `lunco` user can't read it). The hook copies fullchain+privkey
# into /opt/lunco/certs owned by lunco:lunco 0640 on every renewal, then
# restarts this unit. See certbot-deploy-hook.sh.
#
# Fail-loud: if these are set but unreadable/invalid, the server PANICS on
# boot (it refuses to serve a fallback self-signed cert browsers would reject).
# Unset BOTH to run a dev self-signed cert instead.
LUNCO_TLS_CERT=/opt/lunco/certs/fullchain.pem
LUNCO_TLS_KEY=/opt/lunco/certs/privkey.pem

# --- Logging -----------------------------------------------------------------
# Override the unit's default if you need to chase a subsystem, e.g.:
# RUST_LOG=info,lunco_networking=debug,lightyear=warn
RUST_LOG=info

# --- Optional: eager MSL preload ---------------------------------------------
# Modelica compile is lazy by default (compiles classes on demand). If your
# scene's cosim models need the full Modelica Standard Library resident up
# front, uncomment. Costs startup time + RAM; leave off unless a model needs it.
# LUNCO_MODELICA_PRELOAD_MSL=1
